  "help_about": "About",
  "help_appInfo": "App to automatically forward incoming SMS.\nAdditional features: notifications for incoming calls and battery status.",
  "help_info": "Intro",
  "help_info_01": "With this app, you can forward messages to a Telegram bot or an email address with SMTP access. You can add multiple bots or email addresses!",
  "help_info_02": "A forwarding rule is created for each connection — it defines which messages to send and where. Rules can be duplicated, enabled, or disabled as needed.",
  "help_info_03": "The app checks active rules and attempts to forward a new message. If it fails due to technical reasons (e.g., no internet), the app will retry later.",
  "help_info_04": "Make sure to keep the internet connection enabled for the app to work.",
  "help_opts_01": "First, select the events you want to forward. As the app runs, a message is generated and sent for each event according to the specified rules.",
  "help_opts_02": "Permanent background mode improves reliability of message delivery (especially for system notifications), but significantly increases battery consumption. In this mode, a persistent notification appears in the notification shade. Not recommended to enable unless necessary.",
  "help_opts_03": "When forwarding messages from multiple phones, you can set a device label — it is sent along with the message to identify the receiving phone.",
  "help_opts_04": "It is recommended to disable battery optimization for the app, since the system may restrict background activity to save power.",
  "help_tbot": "Connecting a Telegram Bot",
  "help_tbot_01": "If you don't have a Telegram bot yet, use @BotFather bot to create one and get its token. It's simple and free.",
  "help_tbot_02": "Open a chat with your bot in Telegram, start a conversation, or send any message. This is needed to automatically retrieve the chat id for the next step.",
  "help_tbot_03": "In the app, create a Telegram bot rule and enter the token (you can also set a Chat ID if you know it). Test the settings, then save. A welcome message will arrive upon a successful test.",
  "help_tbot_04": "Done! Everything is set up to forward messages to your bot. Enable the rule and press Start to begin.",
  "help_tbot_05": "There is also an option to set a custom API server URL to use it instead of the official Telegram server.",
  "help_smtp": "Connecting an SMTP Server",
  "help_smtp_01": "It is best to create a dedicated email for message forwarding (not an alias): it will also serve as your login. This is especially relevant for Gmail and similar services.",
  "help_smtp_02": "Create a rule and fill in the connection details. Usually, an 'App Password' is required (generated in your email provider's security settings).",
  "help_smtp_03": "Test and save the settings, enable the rule, and press Start.",
  "help_filters": "Filters",
  "help_filters_01": "You can set filters for sender or message text. A filter is triggered if a sender number/name or text contains the specified characters.",
  "help_filters_02": "There are two modes: whitelist (message is forwarded if at least one filter matches) and blacklist (message is not forwarded if any filter matches). In whitelist mode, if no filters are set, no messages will be forwarded.",
  "help_filters_03": "Use two forward slashes for regex. For example, filter /^\\d*555$/ matches all numbers, that end with 555",
  "help_filters_04": "To check whether a specific message will be forwarded based on the current filters, enter the required sender and/or message text in the input fields and click the button to verify.",
  "help_filters_05": "The specified filters are applied to all event types, not just incoming SMS.",
